%spark.pyspark
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
plt.switch_backend('agg')

delay_sql = sqlContext.sql("""select SUBSTR(c.description, 0, 15) as Carrier, WorkDayDelay, WeekendDelay from
   (select ceil( avg(f.ArrDelay + f.DepDelay) ) as WorkDayDelay,
   f.UniqueCarrier
   FROM flights f
         WHERE f.DayOfWeek < 6
         GROUP BY f.UniqueCarrier ORDER BY WorkDayDelay desc limit 10) t
JOIN 
  (select ceil( avg(f.ArrDelay + f.DepDelay) ) as WeekendDelay, 
   f.UniqueCarrier 
   FROM flights f 
         WHERE f.DayOfWeek > 5 
         GROUP BY f.UniqueCarrier) t1 
ON t.UniqueCarrier = t1.UniqueCarrier 
JOIN carriers c on t.UniqueCarrier = c.code order by WeekendDelay desc, WorkDayDelay desc 
""")

delay = delay_sql.toPandas()

fig = plt.figure()
color_range_days = ["#2966FF", "#61F2FF"]
delay["Average"] = (delay.WorkDayDelay + delay.WeekendDelay) / 2
ax = delay.Average.plot(x='Carrier', linestyle='-', marker='o')
plot = delay.plot(x='Carrier', y=['WorkDayDelay','WeekendDelay'], kind='bar', legend = True,  figsize=(12, 4), color=color_range_days, ax=ax)
fig.add_axes(plot)
show(plt, 1400)

paragraphs.text:
%spark.pyspark

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
plt.switch_backend('agg')

q = """SELECT t.cnt as FlightsAmt, carriers.description as Carrier FROM (
            SELECT count(*) as cnt, flights.UniqueCarrier as carrier_code 
                FROM flights GROUP BY flights.UniqueCarrier LIMIT 6) t 
            LEFT JOIN carriers ON t.carrier_code = carriers.code"""


topFlights = sqlContext.sql(q).toPandas()

fig1, ax1 = plt.subplots()
ax1.pie(topFlights["FlightsAmt"], labels=topFlights["Carrier"], autopct='%1.1f%%')
ax1.axis('equal')
show(plt, 900)
paragraphs.title: Number of flight performed by top companies

paragraphs.text:
%spark.pyspark

N = 10

resultDistance = sqlContext.sql("SELECT SUBSTR(c.description, 0, 15) as Carrier, COUNT(Distance) AS Distance FROM flights f JOIN carriers c ON f.UniqueCarrier = c.code GROUP BY c.description ORDER BY distance DESC LIMIT {}".format(N)).toPandas()

color_range =  ["#2966FF",
 	  "#2E73FF",
 	  "#3380FF",
 	  "#388CFF",
 	  "#3D99FF",
 	  "#42A6FF",
 	  "#47B2FF",
 	  "#4CBFFF",
 	  "#52CCFF",
 	  "#57D9FF",
 	  "#5CE6FF",
 	  "#61F2FF",
      "#66FFFF"]

x = range(N)
_, ax = plt.subplots()
ax.bar(x, resultDistance['Distance'], color=color_range, tick_label=resultDistance['Carrier'])
ax.set_xlabel('Carrier')
plt.xticks(rotation=70)
show(plt, 800)
paragraphs.title: The average Flight Distance per Company
